    • Class com.avaya.csta.binding.ConvertDialStringToE164 extends ch.ecma.csta.CastorObject implements Serializable

      • Serialized Fields

        • _switchName

          java.lang.String _switchName
          Specifies the name of the switch for which the dial string should be converted to an E.164 number. Note that this corresponds to a switch name administered on AE Services OAM, and that a list of switch names can be discovered using a GetLinkStatus request from CallInformationServices. It is highly recommended that a switch name be provided. If a switch name is not provided AES will query each switch dialplan administered in OAM for the first possible conversion rule match and use that switch name to handle the conversion request.

        • _dialStringList

          DialStringList _dialStringList
          A list of one or more dial strings to be converted to E.164. If the switch name is not provided, the first entry in the list will be used to find an appropriate switch name. If a switch name is found that switch name will be used for the remaining list entries.

          E164ConversionResult Parameters
          resultType Always provided CONVERTED indicates that a matching rule was found and the dial string was successfully converted to a E.164 number.         • _originalCallInfo

          OriginalCallInfo _originalCallInfo
          Specifies the Original Call Information.

          Note that information is not repeated in the originalCallInfo, if it is already reported in the CSTA service parameters or in the private data. For example, if the userEnteredCode in the private data is the original userEnteredCode, the userEnteredCode in the originalCallInfo will be null. Only when new userEnteredCode is received and reported in the userEnteredCode, the originalCallInfo will have the original userEnteredCode.

          Note: For the Delivered Event sent to the initiatedCall of a Consultation Call, the originalCallInfo is taken from the existingCall specified in the Consultation Call request. Thus the application can pass the original call information between two calls. The consultedDevice of the Consultation Call must reside on the same switch and must be monitored by the same AE Services.

          The original call information contains the following fields for the DeliveredEvent:

          • reason
          • lookaheadInfo
          • userEnteredCode
          • userData
          • callLinkageData
          • deviceHistory

      • Serialized Fields

        • _rtpAddress

          IPAddress _rtpAddress
          Specifies IPAddress for RTP. This includes the IP address and port number. Specifies the Real Time Protocol address where the media should be directed. Defaults to connector server address so that connector server handles the media. If application wishes to handle the media, then specify an even UDP port address. Optional.

        • _rtcpAddress

          IPAddress _rtcpAddress
          Specifies IPAddress for Real Time Control Protocol. This includes the IP address and port number. Conditional. If no RTP address was specified, then do not specify an RTCP address. If an RTP address was specified, then specify the odd UDP port address that immediately follows the RTP address.

        • _codecsList

          java.util.Vector<E> _codecsList
          Specifies the codec(s) to be used. The preferred set of codecs to be used for media coming to the device and media coming from the device. Possible values are
          • MediaConstants.G711A (G.711 A-law)
          • MediaConstants.G711U (G.711 Mu-law)
          • MediaConstants.G729
          • MediaConstants.G729A
          • MediaConstants.G723
          . Defaults to G.711 A-law and Mu-law, in that order. The G.723 codec may be used only for Client Media Mode (i.e. where the RTP stream is directed to a machine other than the CMAPI connector server and is handled by the application). Multiple codecs can be listed in preferential order. However, a mixture of G.711, G.729 and G.723 cannot be in the list (i.e., the list may contain one or more G.711 codecs or one or more G.729 codecs, but not a mixture of G.711 and G.729.) Also, no conversion between G.711 and G.729 (or G.723) is provided by this API. To choose an appropriate codec set, you may wish to first determine how the device's network region and codecs are administered on Communication Manager. This set should consist of only codecs administered for the device's network region. Optional.

        • _packetSize

          java.lang.Integer _packetSize
          Specifies the size of media packets in milliseconds. Defaults to 20 milliseconds. Possible values are 10-60 in multiples of 10. Recommended to use default. If you don't use default, you must also administer Communication Manager to change the codec of the network region where the phone belongs. Optional.

        • _encryptionListList

          java.util.Vector<E> _encryptionListList
          Specifies a list of encryption algorithms supported for media (RTP). This is either for client media mode or server media mode under exclusive control. Possible values include MediaConstants.AES ("aes") and/or MediaConstants.NOENCRYPTION ("none"). This encryption list specifies the capabilities of the CMAPI endpoint. The actual algorithm that is chosen for a call is dependent on the administered list in Communication Manager. Administration of Media Encryption is done in the Communication Manager ip-codec-set form. Optional.

        • _reason

          java.lang.Integer _reason
          Specifies the reason on the unregister response. Even though the request for the unregisteration of station returns successfully, the reason contains more detailed information on the request. If the station was registered previously, the request returns successfully with the reason indicating the station was idle and the unregistration is in progress. If the station was idle previously, the request returns successfully with the reason indicating the station was idle. In this case, there will be no unregisteration event. If the station was in the process of unregisteration previously, the request returns successfully with the reason indicating the station was in the process of unregisteration. The value for the reason code is defined in the RegisterationConstants.
